# CedarRX - Cursor AI Rules

## Project Context
This is CedarRX, an expert compounding pharmacy providing personalized medications and healthcare services in Twin Falls, Idaho.

## Design System (Reference Only)
When building sections, refer to `DESIGN-AGENT.md` for complete guidelines.
Note: Agent must be explicitly called with @.DESIGN or @DESIGN-AGENT.md

### Colors (ONLY USE THESE)
- Cedar Green: #2D5F4F (primary brand, CTAs)
- Deep Forest: #1E4038 (dark sections, hover)
- Light Cedar: #3D7A64 (accents)
- Warm Cream: #FBF9F6 (main backgrounds - NOT stark white)
- White: #FFFFFF (cards, contrast sections)
- Text: #1A202C (headings), #4A5568 (body)
- ðŸš« NO bright blues, bright reds, stark white backgrounds, black text

### Typography
- All text: Inter (system-ui fallback)
- Headings: Semi-bold (600) or Bold (700)
- Body: Regular (400)
- Light body: Light (300) for subtle text
- Keep it clean, modern, medical-professional

### Aesthetic
- Warm, natural, trustworthy (inspired by Cedar Clinic)
- Cream backgrounds create approachability
- Forest green conveys natural health
- Lots of whitespace and breathing room
- Subtle animations only (medical professional)

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14+ with App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Framer Motion for animations

## Key Files
- `.DESIGN` or `DESIGN-AGENT.md` - Complete design agent
- `AGENT-QUICK-START.md` - Quick reference
- `app/globals.css` - Color system and typography
- `tailwind.config.ts` - Tailwind configuration

## Remember
- Every section should feel warm, natural, and trustworthy
- Use cream backgrounds (not stark white) for warmth
- Cedar green is the hero color
- Animations should be subtle and professional
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Make content editable via config objects
- Trust-first approach for medical/pharmacy context
